# Visioryx Dashboard - Environment
#
# Phone / other devices on your LAN:
# - Leave NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL unset so the browser uses same-origin + Next.js /api rewrite (recommended).
#   If you set it to http://localhost:8000, phones will call their own localhost and API calls fail.
# - Run `npm run dev` (binds 0.0.0.0) and open http://YOUR_LAN_IP:3000 on the phone.
# - Set backend PUBLIC_DASHBOARD_URL (or Admin → Email & SMTP → Public dashboard URL) to
#   http://YOUR_LAN_IP:3000 so QR codes and email links use a host the phone can reach (not localhost).
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8000
# Optional: force QR / enrollment links to this origin (overrides backend public URL)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=http://192.168.1.10:3000
